  "local_port": 35406,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I register my mobile number with UAN?",
  "response": "Registering your mobile number with your Universal Account Number (UAN) is essential for accessing various services provided by the Employees' Provident Fund Organisation (EPFO) in India, such as viewing your EPF balance, downloading your EPF passbook, and receiving important notifications. Below are the step-by-step methods to register your mobile number with your UAN:\n\n---\n\n## **Method 1: Using the EPFO Member Portal**\n\n1. **Access the EPFO Member Portal:**\n   - Open your web browser and navigate to the [EPFO Member Portal](https://unifiedportal-epfindia.gov.in/memberinterface/).\n\n2. **Log In to Your Account:**\n   - Enter your **UAN**, **Password**, and complete the **Captcha** verification.\n   - Click on the **\"Sign In\"** button.\n   - *If you\u2019re logging in for the first time, you might need to activate your UAN by clicking on \u201cActivate UAN\u201d and following the instructions.*\n\n3. **Navigate to the \"Manage\" Section:**\n   - Once logged in, locate the **\"Manage\"** tab in the top menu.\n\n4. **Select \"Registered Mobile Number\":**\n   - Under the \"Manage\" section, click on **\"Registered Mobile Number\"**.\n\n5. **Verify or Update Your Mobile Number:**\n   - If your mobile number is already registered but needs verification or updating, you can edit it here.\n   - To register a new mobile number, ensure the current number field is editable.\n\n6. **Initiate OTP Verification:**\n   - After entering or confirming your mobile number, click on the **\"Verify\"** button.\n   - An **OTP (One-Time Password)** will be sent to the mobile number provided.\n\n7. **Enter the OTP:**\n   - Input the received OTP in the designated field.\n   - Click on **\"Verify\"** to confirm your mobile number.\n\n8. **Confirmation:**\n   - Once verified, a confirmation message will appear indicating successful registration.\n\n---\n\n## **Method 2: Using the UMANG Mobile App**\n\n1. **Download the UMANG App:**\n   - Available for both **Android** and **iOS** devices.\n   - [Google Play Store](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.nsdl.mobile.epfo.umangapp) | [Apple App Store](https://apps.apple.com/in/app/umang/id1354354664)\n\n2. **Open the UMANG App and Select EPFO Services:**\n   - Launch the app and navigate to the **\"EPFO\"** service.\n\n3. **Log In to Your Account:**\n   - Enter your **UAN**, **Password**, and complete the **Captcha** verification.\n   - *First-time users may need to activate their UAN within the app.*\n\n4. **Navigate to \"Register Mobile Number\":**\n   - Within the EPFO section, find and select the option to **\"Register Mobile Number\"**.\n\n5. **Enter Your Mobile Number:**\n   - Input your active mobile number in the provided field.\n\n6. **Receive and Enter OTP:**\n   - An **OTP** will be sent to the entered mobile number.\n   - Enter the OTP in the app to verify your number.\n\n7. **Confirmation:**\n   - A success message will confirm that your mobile number has been registered with your UAN.\n\n---\n\n## **Additional Tips & Information**\n\n- **Ensure Active Mobile Number:** \n  - Make sure the mobile number you\u2019re registering is active and able to receive SMS for OTP verification.\n\n- **Employer\u2019s Role:**\n  - Your employer must have properly linked your UAN with your employment details. If you face issues, consult your HR department.\n\n- **Forgot Password:**\n  - If you\u2019ve forgotten your EPFO portal password, use the **\"Forgot Password\"** option on the login page.\n  - An OTP will be sent to your registered mobile number to reset your password.\n\n- **UAN Activation:**\n  - If your UAN is not yet activated, you can activate it through the EPFO portal or the UMANG app using your UAN and other personal details.\n\n- **Contact EPFO Support:**\n  - For persistent issues, reach out to EPFO's customer support or visit your nearest EPFO office.\n\n---\n\nBy following the above methods, you can successfully register your mobile number with your UAN, ensuring seamless access to your EPF services and timely notifications.",
